<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1891,2034]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,152,410]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Endemic to the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Lucas, E. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L." box="[523,733,1930,1956]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" pagination="352 - 366" refId="ref15003" refString="Sobral, M., Lucas, E., Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. (2009) Myrtaceae. In: Stehmann, J., Forzza, R. C., Salino, A., Sobral, M., Costa, D. P. &amp; Kamino, L. H. Y. Plantas da Floresta Atlantica. Rio de Janeiro, pp 352 - 366." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[608,667,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) from the Northeast to Southern regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1314,1930,1956]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Ashton, P. &amp; Barrie, F. &amp; Holst, B. K. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Matsumoto, K. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Lughadha, E. N. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. H. &amp; Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E." pageId="11" pageNumber="44" refId="ref13244" refString="Govaerts, R., Sobral, M., Ashton, P., Barrie, F., Holst, B. K., Landrum, L., Matsumoto, K., Mazine, F. F., Lughadha, E. N., Proenca, C., Soares-Silva, L. H., Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) World Checklist of Myrtaceae. The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet; http: // www. kew. org / wcsp /. Accessed: 29 July 2010." type="url" year="2010">
Govaerts 
<emphasis box="[151,211,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Sobral, M." box="[294,577,1969,1995]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" pagination="111 - 113" refId="ref14537" refString="Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Sobral, M. (2006) Myrtaceae, In: Barbosa, M. R. V., Sothers, C., Mayo, S., Gamarra-Rojas, C. F. L. &amp; Mesquita, A. C. (eds.). Checklist das Plantas do Nordeste Brasileiro: Angiospermas e Gymnospermas. Ministerio de Ciencia e Tecnologia, Brasilia, pp. 111 - 113." type="book chapter" year="2006">Proença &amp; Sobral 2006</bibRefCitation>
). In the Northeast, it is found in the States of 
<collectingRegion box="[1120,1189,1969,1995]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[1205,1423,1969,1995]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[1292,1352,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[151,297,2008,2034]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Griz, L. M. S. &amp; Machado, I. C. S." box="[312,582,2008,2034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" pagination="197 - 224" refId="ref13394" refString="Griz, L. M. S. &amp; Machado, I. C. S. (1998) Aspectos morfologicos e sindromes de dispersao de frutos e sementes na Reserva Ecologica de Dois Irmaos. In: I. C. Machado, A. V. Lopes, &amp; K. C. Porto (Eds.). Reserva Ecologica de Dois Irmaos: Estudos em um Remanescente de Mata Atlantica em area urbana (Recife-Pernambuco-Brasil). Editora Universitaria da Universidade Federal de Pernambuco, Recife, pp. 197 - 224." type="book chapter" year="1998">Griz &amp; Machado 1998</bibRefCitation>
), and new records of this species for State of 
<collectingRegion box="[1113,1209,2008,2034]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
are presented here. Trees 
<quantity box="[227,305,152,178]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" unit="m" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 m</quantity>
tall. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1857" box="[558,862,152,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Gomidesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blanchetiana">
<emphasis box="[558,862,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Gomidesia blanchetiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having larger leaves (
<quantity box="[1174,1298,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" unit="cm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 cm</quantity>
long) with attenuate bases and petioles c. 
<quantity box="[509,576,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long; it differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1064,190,216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[889,972,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having a sulcate midvein on the adaxial lamina surface, imbricate, equal and apiculate calyx, lobes, a pilose hypanthium and base of style and globose fruit.
</paragraph>
